article.headline: Long Beach St 95, Cal St-Fullerton 85
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon scored 27 points and Kejuan Johnson added 20 to lead Long Beach State to a 95-85 victory over Cal State Fullerton Thursday. It was the 49ers' (12-5, 3-1 Big West Conference) 10th win in 11 games. The team is tied for first-place with UC Santa Barbara in the conference. With strong inside play from Scott Cutley, Cal State Fullerton (13-4, 4-2) erased a 13-point second-half deficit and took a 70-69 lead on Bobby Brown's two free throws with 7:36 remaining. But the 49ers, led by Nixon, Johnson, Kevin Houston and Sterling Byrd, scored on 12 of their final 14 possessions to retake command of the game and seal the win. Nixon and Johnson combined to make eight of 15 3-pointers and had 15 rebounds. Houston scored 14 points and had six assists, while Byrd finished with 12 points and nine rebounds. Brown, the second leading scorer in the conference, scored a game-high 28 points for the Titans. Cutley scored 19 of his 23 points in the second-half for Cal State Fullerton.
